SIMPLE: exhort
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exhort
<hw>Ex*hort"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Exhorted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Exhorting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>exhortari</ets>;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>hortari</ets> to incite, encourage; cf. F.
<ets>exhorter</ets>. See <er>Hortative</er>.]</ety> <def>To incite by
words or advice; to animate or urge by arguments, as to a good deed or
laudable conduct; to address exhortation to; to urge strongly; hence, to
advise, warn, or caution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Examples gross as earth <qex>exhort</qex> me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let me <qex>exhort</qex> you to take care of yourself.</q>
<rj><qau>J. D. Forbes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exhort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exhort
<hw>Ex*hort"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To deliver exhortation; to use
words or arguments to incite to good deeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With many other words did he testify and <qex>exhort</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts ii. 40.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exhort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Exhort
<hw>Ex*hort"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Exhortation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exhortation</ent>⟦br⟧
